ired for the expected spin-up formation mechanism. An increase of angular\nmomentum from non-gravitational forces after binary formation is a possible\nexplanation. The two components have similar radar reflectivity, suggesting a\nsimilar composition consistent with formation by spin-up. The secondary appears\nto exhibit a larger circular polarization ratio than the primary, suggesting a\nrougher surface or subsurface at radar wavelength scales.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 5 Mar 2015 19:56:35 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Mon, 29 Jun 2015 20:55:16 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-08-06"}
