ty diverges. This result\nholds in both (1+1) and (1+3) spacetime dimensions with a \\emph{milder}\ndivergence for the total energy inside a small region in (1+3) dimensions.\nThese results suggest that the back-reaction effects are significant even in\nthe region \\emph{outside the matter but inside the event horizon}, close to the\nsingularity.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 5 Mar 2015 21:00:14 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Sat, 14 Mar 2015 12:36:13 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Mon, 6 Jul 2015 15:21:34 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-07-07"}
